<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="estimate-vt">estimate <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'estɪmeɪt/    美 /'estɪmeɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>估计；估价；估算：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>estimate sth (at sth):</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They estimate the cost to repair at $800.
他们估计维修费用为800美元。</p><footer>2016 天津改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>be estimated to be / have:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The tree is estimated to be at least 700 years old. 
这棵树估计至少有700年了。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>estimate / it is estimated + (that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The university estimates that living expenses for international students are around $8,450 a year.
大学估算国际生一年的生活费用约8450美元。</p><footer>2013 湖南</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is estimated that 80% of all conversation in English is small talk. 
据估计，英语中80%的谈话都是闲谈。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 1</footer></div></div>